      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;(⌘ -) × 2&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I swear I’m going to wear out that key combination from using it on every product&amp;#x2F;site these days </description>
        
      
      
      
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><strong>(⌘ -) × 2</strong></p><p>I swear I’m going to wear out that key combination from using it on every product&#x2F;site these days to make it passably readable.</p><p>When you shipped, did you read it on a real screen—or did the mock‑ups and metrics say ‘good enough’?</p><p>EDIT: I see <a href="https://jayd.ml/2025/04/30/someone-at-youtube-needs-glasses.html">I’m not the only one feeling this way</a>.</p>]]></content:encoded>
      
      
      
